# Errors, Logging, and Security

Use this rule with `.ai/lifecycle/think.md`, `.ai/lifecycle/plan.md`, `.ai/lifecycle/build.md`, `.ai/lifecycle/review.md`, and `.ai/lifecycle/test.md`.

Before changing error handling, logging, auth, or sensitive-data behavior, identify caller permissions, resource ownership, public error shape, log fields, and failure-path tests.

## Error Handling

{{#if isNestJS}}
- Never return res.status() manually from controllers.
- Throw appropriate NestJS `HttpException` classes (e.g., `NotFoundException`, `BadRequestException`).
- Use the global `ExceptionFilter` to catch unhandled errors and format them consistently.
{{else if isExpress}}
- Use an async wrapper to catch rejected promises and pass them to `next(err)`.
- Use a global error-handling middleware `(err, req, res, next)` at the end of the middleware stack.
{{else if isFastify}}
- Define a custom `errorHandler` via `fastify.setErrorHandler()`.
{{else if isHono}}
- Use `app.onError((err, c) => ...)` to catch and format all unhandled exceptions.
{{/if}}

- Never leak internal server errors, database stack traces, or sensitive config values in HTTP responses.
- Map domain errors to standard HTTP status codes (e.g., `EntityNotFound` -> `404`, `ValidationFailed` -> `400`).

## Logging & Observability

- Use structured JSON logging for all production logs.
- Include a `correlation_id` (Trace ID) in all logs associated with a request lifecycle.
- **Never** log PII (Personally Identifiable Information), passwords, tokens, or financial specifics.
{{#if (includes monitoring "sentry")}}
- Send unhandled exceptions and critical errors to Sentry.
{{/if}}
{{#if (includes monitoring "apm")}}
- Ensure APM transaction tracing is wrapped around background jobs and HTTP requests.
{{/if}}

## Security

{{#if (eq auth "jwt-passport")}}
- Validate JWT signatures on all protected routes.
- Extract user IDs from the verified token payload, not from request bodies.
{{else if (eq auth "session")}}
- Ensure session cookies are set with `HttpOnly`, `Secure`, and `SameSite=lax/strict` flags.
- Use a secure session store (e.g. Redis), not memory storage for production.
{{else if (eq auth "oauth2-provider")}}
- Trust identity verification from the external Auth provider.
- Validate incoming webhooks or session claims tightly.
{{/if}}

- Always enforce authorization (who is making the request) **and** resource ownership (are they allowed to touch this specific record ID?).

## Review Requirements

- Authentication and authorization impact are checked separately.
- Allowed and denied cases are tested or manually checked.
- Logs include useful operational context without secrets, tokens, credentials, or full sensitive payloads.
- Public errors remain consistent and safe.

## Must Avoid

- Assuming authentication implies authorization.
- Logging PII, passwords, tokens, raw credentials, or sensitive financial details.
- Returning stack traces, SQL errors, provider internals, or config values to clients.
- Swallowing errors without visibility or remediation path.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Authn/authz, error shape, and log behavior are explicit.
- Sensitive data handling is checked.
- Failure paths are testable or manually checkable.
- Observability changes preserve request correlation.
